LONGER BACKSWING = LONGER DRIVE… TRY THIS❗️
•
•
⛳️Are you like every golfer and you are wanting to drive the ball longer? Having a longer backswing will help with that. Try this simple drill!
•
•
🏌🏻Grab your driver and keep the head cover on for this! Put your golf bag about 2 inches behind your right foot (left foot for lefties) and make a backswing to about lead arm parallel. From there, you’re going to turn and sink your hip into the golf bag, creating the stretch and continuing to lengthen the back swing more and more! 
•
•
✅This will help lengthen that backswing so that you can not only drive the ball further, but straighter.

Everyone needs a good TRIGGER MOVE❗️
•
•
⛳️All sports have a dynamic flow of motion. You see tennis players like Roger Federer moving before returning a tennis serve, baseball players in the field have a routine before every pitch to stay ready, basketball players have a free throw routine to keep that flow of motion and rhythm the same on every shot. Like them, golfers also need this! 
•
•
🏌🏻Mine trigger move is very simple, yet effective. I like to step left, step right, then GO. This will help you be more consistent on the course and eliminate some of the over thinking that can creep into your head before you swing!

Where do you see Bubba Watson finishing❓
•
•
⛳️Bubba Watson is back in action this week playing in The Masters Tournament. Here are 2 things we can learn from his swing that dominated for about a whole decade. 
•
•
🏌🏻First, on his back swing, I want you to notice how his trail hip stays inside of his back foot. And on his downswing, you can see from the illustration that his hips barely slide at all. Instead, he’s simply rotating or “swiveling” the hips inside his lead foot.

Longer backswings lead to longer drives on the golf course❗️

Are you like every golfer and you are wanting to drive the ball longer? 

Having a longer backswing will help with that. 

Try this simple drill!

Grab your driver and keep the head cover on for this! Put your golf bag about 2 inches behind your right foot (left foot for lefties) and make a backswing to about lead arm parallel.
